-Pool","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create multiple ephemeral runners using a multi-document YAML:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["kubectl apply -f deploy\/kubernetes\/examples\/ephemeral-pool.yaml"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This creates 3 runners that auto-destroy after each job completes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Controller Details","level":2,"anchor":"Controller-Details","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Swift controller ("},{"code":"Sources\/spook-controller\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") consists of:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KubernetesClient"}]},{"text":" — Reads service account credentials,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"makes authenticated requests to the K8s API","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reconciler"}]},{"text":" — List+watch pattern with auto-reconnection.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Handles ADDED (clone+start), MODIFIED (retry\/resolve IP),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and DELETED (stop+delete) events","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"NodeManager"}]},{"text":" — Discovers Mac nodes by label, maps to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"HTTP API endpoints, periodic health checks","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"MacOSVMResource"}]},{"text":" — Codable types matching the CRD schema","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The controller is stateless — all state lives in CRD status"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fields and on the Mac nodes themselves."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Mac Node Setup","level":2,"anchor":"Mac-Node-Setup","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each Mac node must run "},{"code":"spook serve","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["# Install Spooktacular","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create a base VM","spook create base --from-ipsw latest","","# Start the HTTPS API (bind to all interfaces for cluster access)","spook serve --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8484 \\","  --tls-cert \/etc\/spooktacular\/tls\/cert.pem \\","  --tls-key \/etc\/spooktacular\/tls\/key.pem","","# Or install as a service for persistence","sudo spook service install base  # for the base VM"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Label Mac nodes in Kubernetes for the controller to discover:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["kubectl label node mac-01 spooktacular.app\/role=mac-host"]},{"text":"Troubleshooting","level":2,"anchor":"Troubleshooting","type":"heading"},{"text":"VM stuck in Pending","level":3,"anchor":"VM-stuck-in-Pending","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No Mac node has available capacity. Each Mac supports max 2 VMs."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Check node status:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["kubectl logs -n spooktacular-system deployment\/spooktacular-operator"]},{"text":"Connection refused to Mac node","level":3,"anchor":"Connection-refused-to-Mac-node","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Verify ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook serve","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is running and the port is reachable:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["curl -k https:\/\/10.0.1.50:8484\/health"]},{"text":"Provisioning failed","level":3,"anchor":"Provisioning-failed","type":"headin